1.jupyter notebook --generate-config
after this command config file will be created in in this location
C:\Users\saritha.mandala\.jupyter with this name jupyter_notebook_config.py
2.open this file add few lines of code

# set a known, fixed port for server access
c.NotebookApp.port = 8892

## The number of additional ports to try if the specified port is not available.
c.NotebookApp.port_retries = 5

## Shut down the server after N seconds with no kernels or terminals running â€¦
c.NotebookApp.shutdown_no_activity_timeout = 1200

## Supply overrides for the tornado.web.Application that the Jupyter notebook
#  uses.
c.NotebookApp.tornado_settings = {
 "headers": {
     "Content-Security-Policy": "frame-ancestors * 'self'; report-uri /api/security/csp-report"
    }
  }
c.NotebookApp.extra_static_paths = [r'C:\Users\saritha.mandala\AppData\Roaming\jupyter\custom']


3.create custom.css file
/* Hide the left sidebar */
#jp-left-stack {
    display: none !important;
}

/* Expand the notebook to full width */
#jp-main-content {
    margin-left: 0 !important;
}
with this code and save it into C:\Users\saritha.mandala\AppData\Roaming\jupyter here
4. run this command on terminal
jupyter notebook --ip=0.0.0.0 --port=8892
jupyter notebook --notebook-dir=C:\Users\saritha.mandala\Desktop\flask_login\notebooks --ip=0.0.0.0 --port=8892

